 * joachim.falk@gmx.de--2004-systemc-stuff/SystemC-VPC--mainline--0.1--patch-3
   
 - add some example mapping files
   to use them set the environment "VPCCONFIGURATION"
   to one of them
 - created a "fall back" mode:
   - if no mapping file is given a single component 
     is created, all processes are mapped to this
     using a delay of 10 ns
   - using an illegal mapping file will cause an 
     error! >>>>Expertensystem<<<<<
   - in "fall back" mode tracing is impossible
 - changed enum names to upper case

 * joachim.falk@gmx.de--2004-systemc-stuff/SystemC-VPC--mainline--0.1--patch-4
   
 - disable libefence linking
   Linking libefence causes crashes on systemc where libefence is linked
   with libpthread because of quick-thread (SystemC) pthread incompatibilities !

